            "Explain four major functions of District Assemblies in Ghana.\nHighlight four national institutions that are legally mandated to maintain Law and Order in Ghana.",
            "(a) Four functions of District Assemblies in Ghana:\n1. Formulate and execute local developmental plans, budgets, and infrastructural projects (building clinics, local roads, JHS schools).\n2. Maintain local public sanitation and waste disposal systems, ensuring clean markets and streets.\n3. Collect local revenues, including market tolls, property rates, and business licenses to fund local assembly projects.\n4. Enact local bye-laws to regulate public behavior, sanitation, transport, and safety within the district.\n\n(b) Four institutions that maintain Law and Order in Ghana:\n1. The Ghana Police Service: The primary national body responsible for preventing crime, arresting offenders, and keeping public peace.\n2. The Ghana Armed Forces: Consists of the Army, Navy, and Air Force, protecting the country from external security threats and territorial invasions.\n3. The Judiciary (Courts): Interprets laws and administers fair, impartial justice, legally settling disputes to prevent lawlessness.\n4. The Ghana Prisons Service: Manages correction facilities, safely holding and rehabilitating convicted criminals to protect the public.",
            "4 District Assembly functions: 12 Marks\n4 Law/Order institutions: 8 Marks\nTotal: 20 Marks", 20),

