            "As a Human Resource Manager, what four measures would you put in place to develop the skills and competences of employees?\nIdentify the two main types of human resource and explain each type.",
            "(a) Four measures to develop employee skills and competences:\n1. Sponsoring Regular In-service Training: Organizing continuous training workshops, technical courses, and software bootcamps.\n2. Mentorship and Job Shadowing: Pairing junior employees with seasoned, experienced senior executives for direct learning.\n3. Supporting Sabbaticals/Higher Education: Providing study leaves and financial support for staff to pursue masters or specialized diplomas.\n4. Sponsoring Educational Conferences: Funding employee participation in international industry summits to learn global best practices.\n\n(b) (i) Two main types of human resource:\n1. Skilled human resource.\n2. Unskilled human resource.\n\n(ii) Explanations:\n- Skilled human resource: Refers to professionals and workers who have acquired high-level formal academic, technical, or professional training to perform complex intellectual and technical jobs (e.g. surgeons, engineers, pilots, teachers).\n- Unskilled human resource: Refers to workers who have little or no formal technical training or academic qualifications and perform manual, routine, or repetitive physical labors (e.g. cleaners, farm hands, load carriers/kayayei).",
            "4 HR skills development measures: 12 Marks\n2 HR types identified: 4 Marks\n2 HR types explained: 4 Marks\nTotal: 20 Marks", 20),

        theory(5, "Government & Citizenship",
            "Highlight four major features of Ghana's Fourth Republic.\nList four reasons explaining the high importance of Science and Technology Education in Ghana.",
            "(a) Four major features of Ghana's Fourth Republic:\n1. Democratic Political Stability: It has enjoyed uninterrupted democratic governance and multiple peaceful transitions of power since January 7, 1993.\n2. Supreme 1992 Constitution: Governed under a written constitution that establishes separation of powers and checks and balances.\n3. Vibrant Multi-Party System: Allows multiple political parties (predominantly NPP and NDC) to compete freely in national elections.\n4. High Freedom of Media: Guarantees free expression, allowing numerous private radio, TV, and social media houses to report freely without censorship.\n\n(b) Four reasons for the importance of Science and Technology Education:\n1. Modern Job Opportunities: Trains the youth for high-paying, in-demand technical fields like software development, engineering, and data science.\n2. Agricultural Mechanization: Develops scientific methods, high-yielding crops, and automatic tools to boost food production.\n3. Efficient Healthcare: Equips local medical professionals to operate modern diagnostic gear, improving national health treatment.\n4. Industrial Growth: Enables the design of local machinery and software to process raw materials, reducing dependence on foreign imports.",
